This torrent installs a rootkit via the install.exe file, not the crack. Since DCrack provided the crack and presumably got the install.exe file somewhere else, he may not know anything about the rootkit. On a WIN 7 64 OS, the MBR rewrite will fail, but the MBR will become corrupt, which will destroy the partition and render the OS unbootable. A simple MBR rewrite for Win 7 (insert OS install disk, choose Repair) will fix it. XP and VISTA users need an MBR repair tool to fix theirs (use Hiren) unless the infected MBR is made inaccessible. There is only one way to hack an MBR on Win 7 64 and it's not well known, which is why this hack failed. But it still did its damage.

More on MBR hack. Insallation of the rootkit on anything other than Win 7 64, will succeed and you may never known you've been hacked. You should be able to remove the rootkit by simply repairing the MBR. Use this free one at http://www.sysint.no/products/Download/tabid/536/language/en-US/Default.aspx. Hope this helps.
